{"parse":{"title":"Rondo (game)","pageid":55819565,"revid":813947560,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>A <b>rondo</b> is a type of <a href=\"/wiki/Game\" title=\"Game\">game</a>, similar to <a href=\"/wiki/Keep_away\" title=\"Keep away\">keep away</a>, that is used as a <a href=\"/wiki/Training\" title=\"Training\">training</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Physical_exercise\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Physical exercise\">drill</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Association_football\" title=\"Association football\">association football</a> (soccer). In a rondo, one group of players is tasked with keeping <a href=\"/wiki/Possession_(sports)\" title=\"Possession (sports)\">possession</a> of the ball while completing a series of <a href=\"/wiki/Passing_(association_football)\" title=\"Passing (association football)\">passes</a>, while a smaller group of players (sometimes a single player) tries to take possession.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Clarke_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Clarke-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Rondos take place in close proximity, with the possessing group often circled around the opposing group.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Townsend_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Townsend-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Unlike other possession games, in a rondo, players occupy predetermined <a href=\"/wiki/Position_(team_sports)\" title=\"Position (team sports)\">positions</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Baker_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Baker-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Rondos are said to improve player decision making, coordination, team play, creativity, competitiveness, and physical conditioning.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Baker_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Baker-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The exercise is used by major football organizations including <a href=\"/wiki/FC_Barcelona\" title=\"FC Barcelona\">FC Barcelona</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/AFC_Ajax\" title=\"AFC Ajax\">Ajax</a>, and has been credited with remaking the modern game.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Townsend_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Townsend-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Dutch player and coach <a href=\"/wiki/Johan_Cruyff\" title=\"Johan Cruyff\">Johan Cruyff</a>, who implemented the rondo at Barcelona, described the drill: \"Everything that goes on in a match, except shooting, you can do in a rondo. The competitive aspect, fighting to make space, what to do when in possession and what to do when you haven\u2019t got the ball, how to play \u2018one touch\u2019 soccer, how to counteract the tight marking and how to win the ball back.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Townsend_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Townsend-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Barcelona played one of their most famous rondos prior to the <a href=\"/wiki/2011_UEFA_Champions_League_Final\" title=\"2011 UEFA Champions League Final\">2011 UEFA Champions League Final</a>, in which they roundly defeated <a href=\"/wiki/Manchester_United\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Manchester United\">Manchester United</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Townsend_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Townsend-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Rondo_(game)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Clarke-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Clarke_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Clarke, Dave. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.soccercoachweekly.net/soccer-drills-and-skills/what-is-a-rondo-in-soccer/\">\"What is a Rondo in soccer?\"</a>. <i>Soccer Coach Weekly</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">17 November</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Soccer+Coach+Weekly&amp;rft.atitle=What+is+a+Rondo+in+soccer%3F&amp;rft.aulast=Clarke&amp;rft.aufirst=Dave&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.soccercoachweekly.net%2Fsoccer-drills-and-skills%2Fwhat-is-a-rondo-in-soccer%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARondo+%28game%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Townsend-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Townsend_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Townsend_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Townsend_2-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Townsend_2-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Townsend, Jon. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://thesefootballtimes.co/2014/09/01/the-allure-of-the-rondo/\">\"The Allure of the Rondo\"</a>. <i>These Football Times</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">17 November</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=These+Football+Times&amp;rft.atitle=The+Allure+of+the+Rondo&amp;rft.aulast=Townsend&amp;rft.aufirst=Jon&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fthesefootballtimes.co%2F2014%2F09%2F01%2Fthe-allure-of-the-rondo%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARondo+%28game%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Baker-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Baker_3-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Baker_3-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Bak